node.text: Ngl this was pretty well said
@mk_manifesting_king  So if I believe hard enough I can become a chicken🙂
@dustyblue99 your already thinking like a chicken. So you’re already there.

Believe in Fantasy is the possibility. If you can fantasize it, it is possible. The human mind is capable to achieve anything. If you want something or want to create something fantasy is the gateway for creating and creativity. You must first see in your mind for it to be possible. Don’t let fantasy make you feel that you can not reach something to far out of your limits. I see it as a possibility.
@bernd_6802 Fantasy is just meaning for possibility or say it’s possible

A direction to follow of One's fantasy is real; it realtime shows One's own path-- what to do, for what result :  inspiring for the next step-- at this point, if One wants to do it and/or stop-- for what reason soever; capability, scruples, invironment, connection... the resulting bad or good feeling, timing for growing inspiration, before changing direction, 360°-degree possibility, ascending into a Monster of it's own fantasy creation .
This sounds familiar, is this from the book “Audition”?
So the illusory, becomes the attainable—if it’s mutually exclusive to the pairing who reach for it, to be something possible {Greater Together}
I do t like this tbh
All of our inventions, our art, our music, philosophies, ideologies, were once nothing but a fragmented incomplete vision or fantasy in our minds eye.
Not all fantasy is unobtainable. It can help overcome or bypass self doubt.  It depends on if the fantasy is actually obtainable via effort
@myl_s626 you believe in a lot of fantasy and u don't even know it; "the big bang", moon landings, ball earth...u're more mislead as an atheist than even the looniest Christian

@synastyasia mislead by science? The only thing that proved it’s trustworthy so much that it created a device i can use to chat with the dumbest people on earth? Ill take that, at least i don’t have to be dead to see if it tells the truth or not

@myl_s626 mislead by fake science, basically anything that can't be empirically proven and experimentally replicated it's NOT science, so yeah sorry to break it to u but ur big bang fairytale is just that, a fairytale 🤷‍♀️
YEAH people dont like truth eh?
